### Test Document Visibility & Confidential Level
### Phase 1 - Minimal RBAC Implementation

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001/api/v1
@adminToken = YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE
@userToken = YOUR_USER_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Login as admin@acme.local (Admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@acme.local",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### 2. Create normal public document (Admin)
# Expected: Success - anyone can see this
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "file_name": "public-normal-doc.pdf",
  "file_base64": "",
  "document_type_id": 1,
  "confidential_level": "normal",
  "visibility_scope": "public"
}

### 3. Create confidential public document (Admin)
# Expected: Success - visible to all but marked confidential
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "file_name": "confidential-public-doc.pdf",
  "file_base64": "",
  "document_type_id": 1,
  "confidential_level": "confidential",
  "visibility_scope": "public"
}

### 4. Create secret private document (Admin)
# Expected: Success - only owner + admin can see
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "file_name": "secret-private-doc.pdf",
  "file_base64": "",
  "document_type_id": 1,
  "confidential_level": "secret",
  "visibility_scope": "private"
}

### 5. Create secret public document (Admin)
# Expected: Success - but only owner + admin can see (secret overrides public)
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "file_name": "secret-public-doc.pdf",
  "file_base64": "",
  "document_type_id": 1,
  "confidential_level": "secret",
  "visibility_scope": "public"
}

### 6. List documents as Admin
# Expected: See all documents (4 documents)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 7. Login as regular user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@acme.local",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### 8. List documents as regular user
# Expected: Only see public/normal and public/confidential documents (2 documents)
# Should NOT see: secret documents (private or public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 9. Try to access secret document as regular user
# Expected: 403 DOCUMENT_ACCESS_DENIED
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/3
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 10. Access public normal document as regular user
# Expected: Success (200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/1
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 11. Access public confidential document as regular user
# Expected: Success (200) - confidential is just a label, public scope allows access
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/2
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 12. Try to access secret public document as regular user
# Expected: 403 DOCUMENT_ACCESS_DENIED - secret level overrides public scope
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/4
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### Test Summary:
# ✅ Admin sees all documents (4)
# ✅ Regular user sees only public/normal + public/confidential (2)
# ✅ Regular user gets 403 on secret documents (regardless of scope)
# ✅ Regular user gets 403 on private documents
# ✅ Owner always sees their own documents
